---
import MainLayout from "../../layouts/main.astro";

import { m } from "../../paraglide/messages.js";
---

<MainLayout class="contentContainer">
  <article class="termsContent">
    <section class="header">
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="lastUpdatedDate">Last updated: 17 July 2026</p>
    </section>

    <section class="termsBody">
      <p>Welcome to readthisshit.fyi ("RTS", "we", "our", or "us").</p>
      <p>
        Your privacy matters to us. This Privacy Policy explains what information we collect, why we collect it, how we use it, and the
        rights you have under the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) and other applicable laws.
      </p>
      <p>RTS is an open source project operated from Finland.</p>
      <p>By using RTS, you acknowledge this Privacy Policy.</p>

      <h2>1. Who We Are</h2>
      <p>Project: readthisshit.fyi</p>
      <p>Website: <a href="https://readthisshit.fyi" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">https://readthisshit.fyi</a></p>
      <p>Owner: Mark Pikaro</p>
      <p>Country: Finland</p>
      <p>Contact: <a href="mailto:admin@readthisshit.fyi">admin@readthisshit.fyi</a></p>
      <p>
        GitHub: <a href="https://github.com/readthisshit-fyi" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
          >https://github.com/readthisshit-fyi</a>
      </p>

      <h2>2. What We Collect</h2>
      <p>The information we collect depends on how you use RTS.</p>

      <h3>Account Information</h3>
      <p>When you create an account, we collect:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>email address;</li>
        <li>username or nickname;</li>
        <li>profile picture, if you choose to upload one;</li>
        <li>authentication information managed by Better Auth;</li>
        <li>session identifiers.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Information You Submit</h3>
      <p>If you use community features, we collect information you choose to publish, including:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>website submissions;</li>
        <li>reviews;</li>
        <li>collections;</li>
        <li>profile information;</li>
        <li>future community content, such as articles or similar resources.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Public content is visible to other users.</p>

      <h3>Technical Information</h3>
      <p>When you visit RTS, we automatically collect technical information such as:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>IP address;</li>
        <li>browser information;</li>
        <li>operating system;</li>
        <li>device information;</li>
        <li>referring website;</li>
        <li>pages visited;</li>
        <li>timestamps;</li>
        <li>session information;</li>
        <li>diagnostic information;</li>
        <li>server logs.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Some of this information is collected by our web server, reverse proxy, authentication system, and security tools.</p>

      <h3>Analytics</h3>
      <p>RTS uses analytics to understand how people use the website and to improve the user experience.</p>

      <p>Analytics may include:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>page views;</li>
        <li>clicks;</li>
        <li>navigation paths;</li>
        <li>session recordings;</li>
        <li>heatmaps;</li>
        <li>feature usage;</li>
        <li>A/B testing;</li>
        <li>performance information;</li>
        <li>anonymous usage statistics.</li>
      </ul>

      <p>Where required by law, analytics are only enabled after you give your consent.</p>

      <p>We do not use analytics to sell your personal information or build advertising profiles.</p>

      <h2>3. Why We Process Your Data</h2>

      <p>We process personal information for the following purposes:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>providing the Service;</li>
        <li>authenticating users;</li>
        <li>preventing spam and abuse;</li>
        <li>protecting the security of RTS;</li>
        <li>reviewing website submissions;</li>
        <li>moderating community content;</li>
        <li>improving features and usability;</li>
        <li>diagnosing bugs and technical problems;</li>
        <li>performing analytics;</li>
        <li>responding to support requests;</li>
        <li>complying with legal obligations.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>We never sell your personal information.</p>

      <h2>4. Legal Basis for Processing</h2>
      <p>Under the GDPR, we process personal information using one or more of the following legal bases:</p>

      <h3>Contract</h3>
      <p>We process information necessary to provide your account and the features you request.</p>
      <p>Examples include:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>authentication;</li>
        <li>account management;</li>
        <li>session management;</li>
        <li>website submissions;</li>
        <li>reviews.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Legitimate Interests</h3>
      <p>We process certain information to operate, secure, maintain, and improve RTS.</p>
      <p>Examples include:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>server logs;</li>
        <li>fraud prevention;</li>
        <li>abuse detection;</li>
        <li>debugging;</li>
        <li>service monitoring;</li>
        <li>moderation.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>We balance these interests against your rights and freedoms.</p>

      <h3>Consent</h3>
      <p>Some processing requires your consent.</p>
      <p>Examples include:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>optional analytics;</li>
        <li>heatmaps;</li>
        <li>session recordings;</li>
        <li>future optional cookies.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>You may withdraw your consent at any time.</p>

      <h3>Legal Obligations</h3>
      <p>We may process information when required to comply with applicable laws or legal requests.</p>

      <h2>5. Cookies</h2>
      <p>RTS uses cookies to provide the Service.</p>

      <h3>Essential Cookies</h3>
      <p>These cookies are required for RTS to function.</p>
      <p>Examples include:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>authentication;</li>
        <li>session management;</li>
        <li>security.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Without these cookies, some features will not work.</p>

      <h3>Analytics Cookies</h3>
      <p>Analytics cookies help us understand how RTS is used.</p>
      <p>They help us improve navigation, usability, performance, and accessibility.</p>
      <p>Where required by law, these cookies are only used after you give consent.</p>
      <p>You can change your cookie preferences at any time if cookie controls are available.</p>

      <h2>6. Third-Party Services</h2>
      <p>RTS relies on trusted third-party services to operate.</p>
      <p>Depending on the features you use, your information may be processed by:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Cloudflare, for DNS, caching, network security, and performance.</li>
        <li>Better Auth, for authentication and session management.</li>
        <li>GitHub, for hosting the source code and receiving bug reports or feature requests.</li>
        <li>Umami Analytics, for privacy-focused website analytics.</li>
        <li>Email providers used to send authentication emails and other service-related messages.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>These providers process information only as needed to provide their services.</p>
      <p>
        Some providers may process information outside the European Union. Where required, we use appropriate safeguards to protect your
        information.
      </p>

      <h2>7. Who Has Access to Your Data</h2>
      <p>Access to personal information is limited to people who need it to operate RTS.</p>
      <p>This includes:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>the project owner;</li>
        <li>developers working on RTS;</li>
        <li>moderators, only when access is necessary to perform moderation duties.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Everyone with access is expected to handle personal information responsibly and only for legitimate project purposes.</p>
      <p>Access levels differ depending on each person's role.</p>

      <h2>8. Sharing Your Information</h2>
      <p>We do not sell your personal information.</p>
      <p>We do not rent your personal information.</p>
      <p>We do not share your personal information for advertising.</p>
      <p>We only share information when:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>it is necessary to provide the Service;</li>
        <li>you ask us to do so;</li>
        <li>a trusted service provider processes information on our behalf;</li>
        <li>the law requires us to do so;</li>
        <li>it is necessary to investigate abuse, fraud, or security incidents.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Public content, including reviews, website submissions, profile information, and similar community content, is visible to other
        users.
      </p>

      <h2>9. Data Retention</h2>
      <p>
        We keep personal information only for as long as necessary to operate RTS, comply with legal obligations, resolve disputes, improve
        the Service, and protect the community.
      </p>
      <p>Different types of information may be kept for different periods.</p>
      <p>Examples include:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>account information while your account exists;</li>
        <li>server logs for security, debugging, and abuse prevention;</li>
        <li>backups for disaster recovery;</li>
        <li>analytics data to improve RTS;</li>
        <li>moderation records when needed to enforce our rules.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>When information is no longer needed, we delete or anonymize it where reasonably possible.</p>

      <h2>10. Account Deletion</h2>
      <p>You may request deletion of your account by contacting us.</p>
      <p>When your account is deleted:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>your personal information is anonymized where reasonably possible;</li>
        <li>your public profile becomes "Deleted User";</li>
        <li>your reviews are removed;</li>
        <li>technical records and backups may remain until they are automatically replaced or deleted.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Some information may be retained when required by law or for legitimate security purposes.</p>

      <h2>11. Security</h2>
      <p>We take reasonable steps to protect your information.</p>
      <p>These measures include:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>encrypted HTTPS connections;</li>
        <li>authentication security;</li>
        <li>access controls;</li>
        <li>server monitoring;</li>
        <li>security updates;</li>
        <li>logging and abuse detection.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>No system is completely secure.</p>
      <p>While we work to protect your information, we cannot guarantee absolute security.</p>

      <h2>12. Your Rights</h2>
      <p>
        If you are located in the European Economic Area, the United Kingdom, or another region with similar privacy laws, you have rights
        regarding your personal information.
      </p>
      <p>Depending on your situation, these rights include:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>access to your personal information;</li>
        <li>correction of inaccurate information;</li>
        <li>deletion of personal information;</li>
        <li>restriction of processing;</li>
        <li>objection to certain types of processing;</li>
        <li>withdrawal of consent;</li>
        <li>data portability;</li>
        <li>filing a complaint with your local data protection authority.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>If RTS does not provide a self-service feature for one of these rights, you may contact us by email.</p>
      <p>We will respond within the time required by applicable law.</p>

      <h2>13. Children's Privacy</h2>
      <p>RTS is intended for a general audience.</p>
      <p>We do not knowingly collect personal information from children in violation of applicable law.</p>
      <p>If you believe a child has provided personal information unlawfully, please contact us.</p>

      <h2>14. International Transfers</h2>
      <p>Some of the services used by RTS may process information outside Finland or the European Union.</p>
      <p>
        When personal information is transferred internationally, we take reasonable steps to ensure it receives an appropriate level of
        protection under applicable law.
      </p>

      <h2>15. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
      <p>RTS will continue to evolve.</p>
      <p>When this Privacy Policy changes, we will update the "Last updated" date at the top of this page.</p>
      <p>
        If a change significantly affects how your personal information is processed, we will make reasonable efforts to notify registered
        users before the change takes effect.
      </p>

      <h2>16. Contact</h2>
      <p>If you have questions about this Privacy Policy, your personal information, or your rights, you can contact us.</p>
      <p>Email</p>
      <p><a href="mailto:admin@readthisshit.fyi">admin@readthisshit.fyi</a></p>
      <p>
        GitHub: <a href="https://github.com/readthisshit-fyi" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
          >https://github.com/readthisshit-fyi</a
        >
      </p>
      <p>
        Privacy requests, GDPR requests, copyright notices, moderation appeals, bug reports, and feature requests are welcome through the
        appropriate contact method.
      </p>
      <p>Thank you for trusting RTS with your information. We believe privacy should be clear, understandable, and respectful.</p>
    </section>
  </article>
</MainLayout>

<style lang="scss">
  .contentContainer {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    padding: 0;
  }

  .termsContent {
    width: 100%;
    max-width: var(--max-content-width);
    padding: 0 20px;

    .header {
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      justify-content: center;
      align-items: flex-start;
      height: auto;
      padding: 70px 0;

      h1 {
        color: var(--text);
        font-size: 48px;
        font-style: normal;
        font-weight: 600;
        line-height: normal;
        text-align: left;
        width: 100%;
        margin: 0 0 20px 0;
      }

      .lastUpdatedDate {
        text-align: left;
        width: 100%;
        font-size: 14px;
        color: var(--dimmed-text-two);
        padding: 0;
        margin: 0;
      }
    }

    .termsBody {
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 20px;
      padding-bottom: 100px;

      p {
        color: var(--text);
        font-size: 16px;
        line-height: 1.6;
        margin: 0;

        strong {
          font-weight: 600;
        }

        a {
          color: var(--text);
          text-decoration: underline;
          transition: opacity 0.2s ease;

          &:hover {
            opacity: 0.7;
          }
        }
      }

      h2 {
        color: var(--text);
        font-size: 24px;
        font-style: normal;
        font-weight: 600;
        line-height: normal;
        margin: 0;
        padding: 0 0 0 16px;
        border-left: 4px solid var(--text);
        opacity: 0.8;
      }

      h3 {
        color: var(--text);
        font-size: 20px;
        font-style: normal;
        font-weight: 600;
        line-height: normal;
        margin: 0;
        padding: 0 0 0 12px;
        border-left: 2px solid var(--text);
        opacity: 0.8;
      }

      ul {
        list-style: none;
        padding-left: 20px;
        margin: 0;

        li {
          color: var(--text);
          font-size: 16px;
          line-height: 1.6;
          margin-bottom: 10px;
          position: relative;
          padding-left: 15px;

          &::before {
            content: "•";
            position: absolute;
            left: 0;
            font-weight: bold;
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .termsContent {
      .header {
        padding: 40px 0;

        h1 {
          font-size: 32px;
        }

        .lastUpdatedDate {
          font-size: 12px;
        }
      }

      .termsBody {
        gap: 16px;
        padding-bottom: 50px;

        p {
          font-size: 14px;
        }

        h2 {
          font-size: 20px;
        }

        h3 {
          font-size: 17px;
        }

        ul li {
          font-size: 14px;
        }
      }
    }
  }
</style>
